The opening of the mantle cavity (35 to 37 μm wide, 20 to 40 μm high) is almost terminal (
Figure 7 E
). The epithelium of the mantle cavity is folded. The folds are interpreted as respiratory folds because of their position, shape, and the presence of ciliated cells. There are six or eight folds. The rectum (dorsal) and the spawning duct (ventral) open centrally into the mantle cavity. Remains of a posterior mass of glandular cells were found but their function could not be determined.
